      "id": "196d3d2f62851350",
      "subject": "Re: Credit Building for New Immigrants",
      "from": "mcp.test.dki2@gmail.com",
      "date": "Thu, 15 May 2025 05:02:20 -0700",
      "snippet": "Hi Maria, Thank you for reaching out about ways to help newcomers establish credit in the United States. Below are some practical steps that have worked well for members of our community: 1. Secured",
      "body": "Hi Maria,\n\nThank you for reaching out about ways to help newcomers establish credit in the United States. Below are some practical steps that have worked well for members of our community:\n\n1. Secured credit card – Many banks and credit unions offer a card that requires a refundable security deposit. On-time payments over several months help build a positive record, and some issuers will convert the card to unsecured status later.\n\n2. Authorized-user status – If a trusted friend or relative with strong credit adds the newcomer as an authorized user on an established, well-managed card, the account’s history can quickly populate the newcomer’s credit file.\n\n3. Credit-builder loan – Community-oriented credit unions often provide small loans (sometimes called share-secured or savings-secured). Each monthly payment is reported to the credit bureaus, and at the end of the term the borrower receives the accumulated funds.\n\n4. Report rent and utilities – Several third-party services allow tenants to have consistent rent, utility, or cellphone payments reported to the bureaus, adding more positive data points.\n\n5. Keep balances low and pay on time – Payment history and credit-utilization ratio weigh heavily in credit-score calculations. Aim to pay every bill before the due date and keep revolving balances well below the limit.\n\n6. Limit new applications – Each credit application triggers a hard inquiry. Spacing out applications and focusing on products designed for credit-building will protect the score while it grows.\n\nWith consistent use of these strategies over six to twelve months, we’ve seen newcomers progress from having no U.S. credit file to a healthy score that unlocks mainstream financial products.\n\nFeel free to pass these tips along, and let me know if you’d like any additional resources or workshop materials.\n\nWarm regards,\nJohn\n"
    },
    {
      "id": "196d3d1a67801cc6",
