      "date": "Thu, 15 May 2025 05:00:54 -0700 (PDT)",
      "snippet": "Address not found Your message wasn&#39;t delivered to mark@trustwellbank.com because the address couldn&#39;t be found, or is unable to receive mail. The response from the remote server was: 550 No",
      "body": "Hi Mark,\r\n\r\nThanks for reaching out.\r\n\r\nBelow is a concise overview of the standard procedure we follow when\r\nhandling customer inquiries, along with the protocol for reporting any\r\nissues that arise:\r\n\r\n1. Verify the customer’s identity using the approved verification\r\nmethods (e.g., two pieces of ID and the standard security questions).\r\n2. Log the inquiry in the CRM so the interaction is tracked from the start.\r\n3. Resolve the request if it falls within your authority and is\r\ncovered by routine policy.\r\n4. For questions that require additional support or exceptions, create\r\na ticket with our internal help desk (internal-help@trustwellbank.com)\r\nso the case can be routed to the right team.\r\n5. Once resolved, add a brief summary of the outcome to the CRM record\r\nso future interactions have the full context.\r\n\r\nIssue-reporting protocol\r\n• Capture a brief description of the problem, any relevant account\r\ndetails, and supporting documentation or screenshots.\r\n• Submit the information to the help desk using the same ticketing\r\nsystem noted above.\r\n• If the matter is time-sensitive, refer to the branch-manager contact\r\nlist for a direct escalation channel.\r\n\r\nAdditional resources\r\n• “Bank Procedures Overview” (internal wiki) – a quick refresher on\r\nthe main steps and escalation paths.\r\n• The help-desk knowledge base – searchable articles that address\r\ncommon scenarios.\r\n\r\nLet me know if you have any other questions. I’m happy to walk through\r\nspecific cases or point you to additional materials.\r\n\r\nBest regards,\r\nJane\r\n"
